<TEXT>
a new law will allow greece to try a 
palestinian the united states wants extradited in connection with 
the bombing of an american airliner a member of parliament says 
the bill was approved unanimously by an allparty parliamentary 
committee friday and will become law after a debate in parliament 
next week said the lawmaker who spoke on condition of anonymity 
the legislation appeared designed to prevent the extradition of 
palestinian mohammed rashid wanted by the united sates for 
allegedly planting a bomb that exploded in a pan am airliner flying 
over hawaii in 1982 a japanese teenager was killed by the blast 
and 15 other passengers were wounded 
the rashid affair has become a sensitive issue between greece 
and the united states since his arrest at athens airport in 1988 
he has been awaiting extradition since may 1989 
</TEXT>
