<TEXT>
hungarys prime minister josef antall 
says soviet compensation demands for withdrawing troops from his 
country are unreasonable 
antall on friday also threatened that hungary would leave the 
sovietled warsaw pact if it remained a military organization 
we want to abolish the military structure of the warsaw pact 
if this doesnt happen we will leave it by the end of next year 
antall said in an interview broadcast on finnish national radio 
antall said the soviet union demanded over 4 million for 
facilities and equipment left behind by 50000 soviet soldiers who 
have begun withdrawing from hungary which elected a noncommunist 
government in march 
we think these demands are unreasonable as they the soldiers 
have used old hungarian buildings damaged them and polluted the 
environment said antall in helsinki for a meeting of 
conservative european leaders 
