<TEXT>
when the airmen yelled go get em 
genrul h norman schwarzkopf couldnt resist 
well get em all right he said then he turned quickly to 
correct himself mindful of his mission and the group of reporters 
trailing him 
were going to get them when they come across the border 
said the commander of the us forces marshalling in saudi arabia 
south of the border with iraqioccupied kuwait 
schwarzkopf who set up his command post in saudi arabia just 
days ago paid his first visit to the troops in the field friday 
his nickname is bear and he can be blunt and gruff but on 
friday he tried a more grandfatherly approach putting his arm 
around troops and commanders alike 
he assured them of the worlds support and promised to make 
their stay in the desert as comfortable as possible as they face 
off against the iraqis who invaded kuwait on aug 2 
he had a simple message to the troops 
our job is to get it over as fast as we can he told a group 
of airmen 
after air force a10 pilots told him their tankkilling jets 
could exact a heavy toll on the iraqi armored divisions 
schwarzkopf nooded in approval before fighting goodnaturedly for 
his branch of the service 
try and leave a few for the army will you he quipped as he 
left 
schwarzkopf spoke softly when telling a group of marines about 
the crash of one of the huge c5 galaxy transports in west germany 
on wednesday in the operation desert shield airlift thirteen of 
the 17 americans aboard were killed 
he can shift gears quickly 
at the news conference he was asked if the united states was 
getting military help from israel the enemy of the arab world 
no was the answer next question 
he said he wasnt worried about us troops adjusting to the 
desert climate where temperatures can shoot up to 120 degrees 
theyre not potted plants or greenhouse shrubs he chided 
for iraqi forces schwarzkopf had nothing but bad wishes but he 
delivered them in an animated exchange with reporters 
i hope theyre hungry and i hope theyre thirsty and i hope 
theyre out of ammo he said and i hope they feel bad about 
what they did because they should 
