1949 
both the communists and nationalists regard taiwan as a chinese 
province 
hau said the nationalists would enact laws based on the new 
formula to govern trade cultural and other civilian exchanges 
between taiwan and china such exchanges have increased recently 
officials said one main area to be covered would be the 
repatriation of an increasing number of mainland chinese who have 
entered taiwan illegally to seek a better life at present there 
are no laws covering them 
