speeches 
vatican officials say the pope will speak on aids which is 
particularly widespread in africa 
the pope has expressed solidarity with aids sufferers while 
condemning the sexual behavior that can transmit the disease and 
ruling out the use of condoms as a means of checking its spread 
according to the latest church statistics the number of 
catholics in africa has increased by 50 percent in the past 10 
years to a total of about 75 million or 13 percent of the 
continents population 
moslems are tanzanias largest religious group representing 
about onefourth of the population of 25 million catholics make up 
21 percent with protestants anglicans and animists accounting for 
the rest 
islam and the catholic church the two largest religious groups 
in the world have sometimes been at odds as they compete for 
converts in africa 
