and will try to stabilize the faltering economy within six months 
the soviet economy is wracked by shortages of everything from 
medicine to cigarettes and citizens are furious politicians are 
pushing for economic reforms of varying speed and scope 
four separate panels are currently working on widely different 
proposals to move the soviet economy from a centrally planned 
command system to one driven primarily by market forces 
we must come out with one program gorbachev said friday 
