months to cut off soviets ability to accumulate hot money the 
term for income derived from black marketeering and other 
activities 
the soviet union suffers from what economists call a ruble 
overhang a supply of rubles far outstripping the supply of goods 
available for purchase 
gorbachev did not say exactly how hot money would be 
controlled and did not specify what other steps were under 
