columbias astronomy mission is off 
until late this week so nasa can fix a link to one of the 
telescopes aboard the shuttle 
the space agency had hoped to launch columbia and its 150 
million astro observatory as early as wednesday but engineers 
determined saturday that the problem could not be corrected as 
easily as hoped and said the earliest date would be thursday 
the communication problem between astros xray telescope and 
launch control was the latest in a series of flaws that have dogged 
nasa for months 
nasa has not launched a shuttle since april when discovery 
carried the flawed hubble space telescope into orbit that is the 
largest gap between flights since after the 1986 challenger 
accident 
at nasas jet propulsion laboratory in pasadena calif 
scientists have been working to control the errant magellan 
spacecraft in orbit around venus commands were radioed across the 
solar system saturday to improve control of the magellan which has 
suffered two long communications blackouts 
at cape canaveral nasa officials said the latest columbia delay 
was not viewed as serious 
one day is not going to make that much of a difference to the 
team its not the first time its happened said lisa malone 
spokeswoman for the national aeronautics and space administration 
theres always a chance youre going to have some kind of 
delay whether its weather or something on the orbiter or 
something on the payload which is what we have here she said 
the countdown for a saturday liftoff was halted thursday night 
after contact was lost with astros xray telescope workers 
entered the cargo bay friday to examine a unit linking the 
instrument with the orbiter and launch controllers 
controllers need to be in constant touch with the xray 
telescope before launch to monitor the pressure and temperature of 
argon a chemical used to keep the scientific instruments cool 
engineers decided saturday they could not restore communications 
by installing a new cable in the unit a sort of electronic box 
but would try replacing a component inside the box that channels 
signals between the telescope and launch control if that doesnt 
work the whole box will be replaced 
workers on saturday also replaced an instrument that measures 
acceleration and vibration the instrument failed to activate 
properly during the countdown 
four of the crew members are astronomers who will operate 
astros three ultraviolet telescopes during the nine to 10day 
flight probing some of the hottest objects in the universe the 
xray telescope will be managed by ground controllers the 
observatory will remain aboard the shuttle 
the astro mission was first scheduled for march 1986 but the 
challenger disaster two months earlier put the flight and all 
others on hold 
after a series of minor delays the mission was rescheduled for 
may 30 excessive amounts of hydrogen leaked during fueling 
however and the flight was called off 
another shuttle atlantis was found to have similar leaks a 
month later prompting nasa to ground the entire threeshuttle 
fleet new fuel lines were installed in columbia and the shuttle 
was moved back to the launch pad last month atlantis launch has 
been rescheduled for november 
columbia must lift off before sept 14 or will have to wait 
until after discoverys flight in october with the sunprobing 
ulysses satellite 
